entries.femaleVariant: Good work. Shitshow's over.
Cuttin' my wires now. See ya in the near future.

entries.femaleVariant: Huhhh…
I got a date with Misty, but... heh, I can't take the metro! How's that gonna look for me?
Aah, savin' my ass, V, thank you. How about I drive you home, eh?
She's all yours. I'm beat as it is.
Let's get outta here. Elevator gets us to the garage direct.
Ahem! V? How did it go? Our client is alive and well?
Oh, almost forgot. Should get Wakako on the holo – tell her the job's done.
Better call Wakako. Get her caught up an' all.
Word's out the NCPD's gonna put Watson on lockdown. If I'm gonna sleep in my own bed tonight, we better put it in fifth.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Leave it to me, " a=". I'm drivin'."/>

entries.femaleVariant: Won't leave you hangin', Jack. But don't get used to it.
She'll live.
'Course she's alive and well. That's what we agreed, isn't it?
Uh, relatively well. Trauma Team took 'er off our hands. She'll recover.
entries.maleVariant: Relatively well. Trauma Team took 'er off our hands. She'll recover.

entries.femaleVariant: Relatively speaking.
Splendid. Your payment awaits you – ready to come and grab whenever you like, even right away. But I guess home is the only place you wish to be now.
The NCPD has surrounded Watson. The district is closed. If you are to make it past the cordon, you must move fast.
Thanks for the heads-up. Swing by to see you later.
[Get in]
Hey, V. I have a job for you.
A client of mine is making an arms deal. He needs... protection.
It could get hot – very hot. The gun dealers are Maelstrom.
Alas, nothing ever transpires as planned with them. You better gear up for this.
So, V – are you... willing?
